adb shell pm list packages
==> lists package names of installed devices

adb devicesw
==> lists connected devices

adb shell pm path com.example.someapp
==> Get path to package

adb pull /data/app/com.example.someapp.apk /tmp
==> Get apk from device

apktool d com.example.a.apk
==> decompile dex code, makes Manifest readable


ES File Explorer gives path to all installed apps
Paid apps might reside in /mnt/asec
aapt l -a CutePuppiesWallpaper.apk ==> Lists Manifest 


python androsim.py -i ~/APKs/Twins/de.esymetric.dailyCalorieBalance-1.apk ~/APKs/Twins/de.esymetric.dailyCalorieBalancePRO-1.apk -d > /tmp/o.txt -e "Lcom/actionbarsherlock/|Lcom/amazon/" > /tmp/o.txt 



keytool -genkey -v -keystore my-release-key.keystore -alias alias_name -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000

jarsigner -verbose -sigalg SHA1withRSA -digestalg SHA1 -keystore my-release-key.keystore my_application.apk alias_name

Vgl. http://developer.android.com/tools/publishing/app-signing.html
